common.dataStructures

Class BiMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • common.dataStructures.BiMap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - - the Key type
    V - - the Value type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<K,V>

    public class BiMap<K,V>
extends java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
implements java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<K,V>
    A BiMap is a Bidirectional Map between the two given generic types. Thus both keys and values exist in a set, so there cannot be duplicate values. Lookup operations use the correct map, so all have O(1) behavior.
    Author:
    Mshnik
